{"count":88,"regions":[{"code":"AD","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Andorra eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.govern.ad","status":"Not started","summary":"Andorra's national identity card (Document Nacional d'Identitat) incorporates digital capabilities and serves as the primary identification document for Andorran citizens. The card is issued by the Andorran government and is accepted as a travel document within the Schengen Area. Andorra is a co-principality with a population of approximately 80,000, situated between France and Spain. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels; broader online integration infrastructure is at an early stage of development.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Andorra"},{"code":"AE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~7M+ users (citizens + residents)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality","Gender","Email Address","Phone"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"UAE Trust Level 2","name":"UAE PASS","officialDocUrl":"https://www.uaepass.ae","status":"Not started","summary":"UAE PASS is the UAE's national digital identity platform, operated by the UAE Identity, Citizenship, Customs and Ports Authority (IICA). The platform is distinguished by its coverage of citizens, residents, and visitors alike. Identity verification is performed via facial biometrics matched against the Emirates ID database. The service is integrated with over 2,000 government and private sector applications. Third-party integration requires prior approval from IICA.","useCases":["IDV","AML","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"United Arab Emirates"},{"code":"AL","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (card) / In Development (eID)","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Albanian eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.e-albania.al","status":"Not started","summary":"Albania's digital identity infrastructure comprises a biometric national identity card, issued since 2009, and the e-Albania government services portal, which provides citizens with online access to public services. As an EU candidate country, Albania has demonstrated strong digital preparedness according to OECD 2025 assessments, and digital identity development is progressing in alignment with EU standards. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels, with broader integration capabilities under development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Albania"},{"code":"AM","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Armenian eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.am","status":"Not started","summary":"Armenia's national identity infrastructure is built around a biometric identity card and the gov.am eGovernment portal, which provides citizens with access to a range of public services online. The national ID card, issued by the Police of the Republic of Armenia, incorporates a chip and serves as the primary document for both physical and digital identification. Armenia maintains a Comprehensive and Enhanced Partnership Agreement with the European Union and has participated in selected regional digital identity initiatives. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels, with broader integration capabilities at an early stage of development.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Armenia"},{"code":"AR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Mi Argentina","officialDocUrl":"https://www.argentina.gob.ar/miargentina","status":"Not started","summary":"Mi Argentina is Argentina's national digital government application, operated by the Ministry of the Interior through the National Registry of Persons (RENAPER). The app provides citizens with digital versions of their mandatory National Identity Document (DNI), driver's licence, and other official credentials, all of which carry full legal equivalence to their physical counterparts. Identity verification is performed at RENAPER offices using biometric matching or remotely via a selfie with liveness detection. 47 million DNI cards are in circulation, covering virtually all Argentine citizens. The Buenos Aires city government additionally operates the miBA platform, which incorporates a blockchain-based decentralised digital identity (QuarkID) for its 3.6 million residents.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Argentina"},{"code":"AT","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2025","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"ID Austria","officialDocUrl":"https://www.id-austria.gv.at","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Not started","summary":"ID Austria is Austria's national digital identity application, operated by the Federal Ministry of the Interior (Bundesministerium für Inneres). It replaces the previous Bürgerkarte and Handy-Signatur systems, offering online authentication and qualified electronic signature capabilities. Launched in April 2025, the application serves as both Austria's primary national digital identity solution and its designated EUDI Wallet implementation. An upgrade of the existing app to full eIDAS 2.0 compliance is confirmed, with Austria classified as one of the more advanced EU member states in terms of EUDI Wallet preparation given its existing live infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Austria"},{"code":"AU","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"75-80% of Australian population via 4 major banks (ANZ, CommBank, NAB, Westpac)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Age Verification","Address","Email Address","Phone","Bank Account Details"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"AU TDIF IP2","name":"ConnectID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.connectid.com.au","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"ConnectID is Australia's bank-backed digital identity service, operated by Australian Payments Plus (AP+) in partnership with the four major Australian banks: ANZ, Commonwealth Bank, NAB, and Westpac. Users authenticate via their existing bank account and selectively share verified identity claims. The service achieved Technology Readiness Level 9 (the highest level) in Australia's 2025 Age Assurance Technology Trial and has been adopted by major platforms for over-16 and over-18 age verification compliance. ConnectID operates on a double-blind model in which neither the bank nor the receiving service has visibility of the other party's information.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Varies by state","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","License Number","Age Verification","Portrait"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2019 (NSW first; QLD ISO-compliant version Nov 2023)","levelOfAssurance":"Varies by state/territory","name":"mDL (state by state issued driver's licences)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.austroads.gov.au","status":"Not started","summary":"Mobile driver's licences (mDLs) in Australia are issued at the state and territory level — not federally — and are accessed through each jurisdiction's own government app (for example the Service NSW app, Queensland's Digital Licence app, and South Australia's mySA GOV). In June 2024 the states, territories and the Commonwealth agreed to align mDLs to the international ISO/IEC 18013-5 standard, coordinated by Austroads, but levels of compliance currently differ by state. New, standards-aligned rollouts are targeted across the remaining jurisdictions through 2025–2026.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~70-75% of Australian population","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Age","Gender","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","name":"myID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.myid.gov.au","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"myID (formerly myGovID) is Australia's government digital identity application, operated by the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) and established under the Digital Identity Act 2024. Users verify their identity by presenting Australian government-issued documents — such as a passport, driver's licence, or Medicare card — at Basic, Standard, or Strong assurance levels, with Strong verification incorporating biometric selfie matching against official government records. Third-party access is currently restricted to public-sector entities; private-sector businesses become eligible to apply for accreditation from 30 November 2026.","useCases":["IDV","AML","KYC","Age Verification"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Australia"},{"code":"AZ","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~3M+ registered users (~35% of Azerbaijani adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2012","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"ASAN eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.e-gov.az","status":"Not started","summary":"ASAN (Azerbaijan Service and Assessment Network) is Azerbaijan's national eGovernment service and identity platform, operated by the State Agency for Public Service and Social Innovations under the President of the Republic of Azerbaijan. The platform is underpinned by a biometric national identity card and provides citizens with access to over 300 government services through a unified digital infrastructure. ASAN was awarded the United Nations Public Service Award in 2015 in recognition of its contribution to public service innovation. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels, with broader integration capabilities limited for organisations outside Azerbaijan.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Azerbaijan"},{"code":"BA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Email Address"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2025","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Bosnia eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.iddeea.gov.ba","status":"Not started","summary":"Bosnia and Herzegovina's national digital identity wallet (e-IDDEEA) was launched in July 2025 by the Agency for Identification Documents, Registers and Data Exchange (IDDEEA). The platform was developed with funding from the EU4DigitalSME initiative and the German government. It is fully aligned with eIDAS standards and supports qualified electronic signatures (QES) carrying legal equivalence to handwritten signatures. The platform enables authentication for a broad range of government and private sector services, including banking, telecommunications, tax, and healthcare. As an EU candidate country, Bosnia and Herzegovina is targeting EUDI Wallet alignment by the extended 2027 deadline.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Bosnia and Herzegovina"},{"code":"BE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Belgium EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://bosa.be","status":"Not started","summary":"Belgium's national EUDI Wallet implementation is based on a confirmed upgrade of the existing MyGov.be platform, endorsed by the Federal Public Service Policy and Support. Belgium is considered one of the more advanced EU member states in terms of EUDI Wallet preparation, benefiting from MyGov.be already being live and a clearly defined upgrade pathway. Full EUDI Wallet compliance is targeted for December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Email Address"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"itsme Basic","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"itsme Basic is a lightweight authentication variant of the itsme platform that confirms a user's identity based on their existing itsme account, without requiring a full document-based identity verification process such as NFC chip scanning. The service returns minimal identity data comprising name and email address.","useCases":["Authentication","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"itsme Standard","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"GA","summary":"itsme is a bank- and telecom-backed digital identity application operated by the Belgian Mobile ID consortium. Identity verification is performed by scanning the NFC chip of a physical ID card or passport via the itsme app, followed by PIN or biometric authentication. The service is available in Belgium, Luxembourg, and the Netherlands, and is widely adopted for regulated onboarding across financial services and age-restricted platforms.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"4% (500k out of 11,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address"],"idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2025","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"myGov.be","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mygov.be","status":"Researching","summary":"myGov.be is Belgium's official government digital portal, providing authenticated access to identity data held in the Belgian national registry. Users authenticate via the Belgian eID card or the itsme application. As a government-operated service, myGov.be retrieves identity data directly from authoritative national registry records, encompassing a broader set of verified attributes than those typically available through private sector identity services.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 60% (0,77M out of 1,3M) Latvia: 55% (1M out of 1,8M) Lithuania: 63% (1,75M out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Smart-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.smart-id.com","status":"Contracting","summary":"Smart-ID is a mobile-based digital identity solution widely used across the Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania, and also available in Belgium, operated by SK ID Solutions. Authentication is performed via the Smart-ID application using a personal PIN. The service is available at Basic and Qualified levels; both levels support eIDAS High level of assurance. Smart-ID is widely adopted as an alternative or complement to SIM-based Mobile-ID across the Baltic states.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Belgium"},{"code":"BG","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Bulgaria EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://egov.bg","status":"Not started","summary":"Bulgaria's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Ministry of e-Government, with a public GitHub repository available. While Bulgaria has formally committed to the EU's December 2026 mandate, substantive technical development has not yet commenced at scale, placing Bulgaria among the higher-risk member states for meeting the deadline in full.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Bulgarian eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.egov.bg","status":"Not started","summary":"Bulgaria's national electronic identity scheme is based on the electronic national identity card, which incorporates an NFC chip and electronic certificates. No standalone consumer-facing digital identity application is currently available for third-party integration. Bulgaria has committed to meeting the EU December 2026 EUDI Wallet mandate; however, substantive technical development of a state-provided wallet has not yet commenced, placing Bulgaria among the higher-risk member states for meeting the deadline.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Bulgaria"},{"code":"BH","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"CPR Digital ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.npra.gov.bh","status":"Not started","summary":"Bahrain's national identity is managed via the Central Population Registry (CPR) number, administered by the Nationality, Passports and Residence Affairs (NPRA). eKey, Bahrain's national authentication system, is built on the CPR number and supports digital identity verification for government and private sector services via multi-factor biometric authentication and PKI smart card. Digital identity verification is currently accessible through government-operated and approved channels; a dedicated consumer-facing digital identity application is not yet publicly available.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Bahrain"},{"code":"BR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":">25% (Brazilian DL holders only)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait","License Category","Document Expiry Date","Document Issue Date"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"BR LGPD Compliant","name":"SERPRO QR Code","officialDocUrl":"https://www.serpro.gov.br","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"GA","summary":"SERPRO QR Code is Brazil's government-backed digital identity verification service, operating via the QR code embedded in the national driver's licence (CNH). The user presents the QR code, which is validated against official government records and optionally supports biometric selfie matching. The underlying repository holds records for over 85 million individuals. Coverage is limited to Brazilian driver's licence holders; national ID QR codes and older licences without QR codes are not supported.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Brazil"},{"code":"BY","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Belarus eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.e-pasluga.by","status":"Not started","summary":"Belarus's national identity card incorporates biometric data including a facial image and fingerprints, and is linked to a state eGovernment portal that provides access to public services. The card serves as the primary identity document for Belarusian citizens. Due to sanctions imposed by the European Union, the United States, and other jurisdictions in response to political developments in Belarus, technical and commercial engagement with Belarusian government digital systems is not currently permissible for entities operating under those jurisdictions.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Belarus"},{"code":"CA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~4.6M registered users (~85% of BC adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"CA PCTF Level 3","name":"BC Services Card","officialDocUrl":"https://id.gov.bc.ca","status":"Not started","summary":"The BC Services Card is Canada's most advanced provincial digital identity solution, issued by the Province of British Columbia and managed by the Identity Services division of Digital Trust & Service BC. It serves as a combined identity card, driver's licence, and CareCard for health services, and is available in both physical and digital forms via the BC Services Card app. The digital version supports Level 3 identity assurance under the Pan-Canadian Trust Framework (PCTF), enabling British Columbians to authenticate securely for government services. As of early 2026, the service has approximately 4.6 million registered users. Canada does not yet have a federal digital identity programme; digital identity is managed at the provincial level, with British Columbia the most advanced jurisdiction. The Digital ID and Authentication Council of Canada (DIACC) is working toward national interoperability under the PCTF standard, with a target of digital credential access for 90% of Canadians by 2031.","useCases":["IDV","AML","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Canada"},{"code":"CH","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Swiss e-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.admin.ch/e-id-act","status":"Not started","summary":"Switzerland's national electronic identity (Swiss e-ID) is issued by the Swiss Confederation under the Federal Office of Justice. The e-ID is stored and presented via swiyu, the official Swiss digital identity wallet application. A public beta of swiyu has been available since March 2025, with full productive launch planned for Q4 2026. The launch was delayed following the narrowly approved e-ID Act referendum on 28 September 2025, with additional safeguards introduced around data encryption and provider transparency. Switzerland is not a member of the EU or EEA and therefore operates outside the eIDAS framework, under Swiss federal law.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Switzerland"},{"code":"CL","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~15M+ registered users (~78% of Chilean adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"ClaveÚnica","officialDocUrl":"https://claveunica.gob.cl","status":"Not started","summary":"ClaveÚnica is Chile's national digital authentication system, developed and operated by the Digital Government Secretariat (SGD) under the Ministry of Finance. It provides a single credential for Chilean citizens to access over 1,800 online public services. Originally introduced in 2010 and officially recognised as a unified national digital identity credential in 2017, ClaveÚnica has over 15 million registered users — the majority of the Chilean adult population. A new national digital identity strategy launched in 2025 aims to broaden private sector participation and establish a hybrid model integrating ClaveÚnica with a future digital identity wallet by 2030. A digital version of the identity card is additionally available via the CedulApp mobile application.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Chile"},{"code":"CO","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Gender"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.registraduria.gov.co","status":"Not started","summary":"Colombia's national digital identity solution is built around the Cédula de Ciudadanía, the mandatory national identity card issued by the National Civil Registry (Registraduría Nacional del Estado Civil). A digital version of the card is available via the Mi Registraduría app and a government portal, enabling citizens to access public services using a QR code linked to their biometric record. The system covers all Colombian citizens aged 18 and above. A new digital identity framework was introduced in 2023 under Law 2155, establishing a legal basis for digital identity and enabling the use of digital credentials for private sector services including banking and telecommunications.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Colombia"},{"code":"CR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.tse.go.cr","status":"Not started","summary":"Costa Rica's national identity card (Cédula de Identidad) is issued by the Supreme Electoral Tribunal (TSE). A digital version is available via the TSE's e-identification service and the Sinpe Móvil banking app, which incorporates identity verification. Costa Rica has one of the most advanced digital government ecosystems in Central America. Digital identity verification is available for government services but private sector integration pathways are limited.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Costa Rica"},{"code":"CY","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (portal) / In Development (eID)","idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"ARIADNI","officialDocUrl":"https://www.ariadni.gov.cy","status":"Not started","summary":"ARIADNI is Cyprus's government digital identity portal, enabling citizens to access public services via username and password authentication. The Cypriot government is additionally developing NFC-enabled electronic certificates on the national identity card. No standalone consumer-facing digital identity application is currently available for third-party integration. Cyprus is developing its digital identity infrastructure in alignment with the EUDI Wallet mandate.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Cyprus EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://ncca.cy/certification/eudi-wallet/","status":"Not started","summary":"Cyprus's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Deputy Ministry of Digital Policy. The existing ARIADNI government portal is expected to serve as a foundation for the wallet, though a formal confirmation of the upgrade pathway to full EUDI Wallet compliance has not yet been published. Cyprus is expected to meet the December 2026 mandate.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Cyprus"},{"code":"CZ","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~5M+ users (~47% of Czech adults with a bank account)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address","Email Address","Phone"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Czech Bank iD","officialDocUrl":"https://www.bankid.cz","status":"Not started","summary":"Czech Bank iD is the Czech Republic's national bank-backed digital identity service, developed by the Czech banking sector in collaboration with the Czech Banking Association and public authorities. Users authenticate using their existing online banking credentials, with identity verification based on procedures already carried out by participating banks such as in-person or video onboarding. The service requires no additional app download or registration. Czech Bank iD is widely used for accessing both public services and private sector platforms across the Czech Republic, with over 5 million eligible users across participating banks.","useCases":["IDV","Authentication","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Czech Republic EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://gov.cz","status":"Not started","summary":"The Czech Republic's national EUDI Wallet programme, known as the DIA EUDI Programme, is under development by the Digital and Information Agency (DIA). A publicly announced project exists, though no public sandbox is yet available for ecosystem testing. The Czech Republic is expected to meet the December 2026 deadline, building on its existing digital identity infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"PL: 68% (22M out of 32,5M > 15) Czechia: 8% (700k out of 9M > 15)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2010","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"MojeID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mojeid.cz","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Contracting","summary":"MojeID is a digital identity system available in Poland and the Czech Republic, enabling users to authenticate via an account with a participating identity provider such as a bank or other registered organisation. The service is widely used for accessing government and private sector digital services in both markets, with significantly higher adoption in Poland than in the Czech Republic. No additional app download or registration beyond an existing account with a participating provider is required.","useCases":["IDV"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Czech Republic"},{"code":"DE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Germany EUDI Wallet (Wallet+)","officialDocUrl":"https://bmds.bund.de/themen/digitaler-staat/digitale-identitaeten/eudi-wallet","status":"Not started","summary":"Germany's national EUDI Wallet, referred to as the State EUDI Wallet (Staatliche EUDI-Wallet), is under development by the Federal Ministry for Digital Affairs and Transport (BMDS). The Digital Identities Act (Digitale-Identitäten-Gesetz), which provides the legal basis for the wallet's introduction, was approved by the German government in May 2026. A public sandbox launched in January 2026, enabling organisations to test key functions and apply specific use cases ahead of the production launch. Germany's federated governmental structure means responsibility is distributed across federal and Länder levels, which has historically been a coordination challenge for digital identity rollouts. The wallet is officially targeted for December 2026, though Germany's own website indicates early 2027 as a more realistic date for full availability.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"100% (document) / 25% (PIN activated)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address","Nationality","Birth Place","Document Expiry Date"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2010","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Personalausweis","officialDocUrl":"https://www.personalausweisportal.de","status":"Open Beta","summary":"The Personalausweis is Germany's mandatory national identity card, issued to all citizens aged 16 and over. While the physical card is held by virtually all eligible Germans, fewer than 25% have activated the eID online function by setting a PIN. As of 17 February 2025, all new applicants automatically receive a PIN letter, and activation rates are expected to increase significantly as a result.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Germany"},{"code":"DK","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["Age Verification","Portrait"],"idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Denmark EUDI Wallet (AltID)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digst.dk","status":"Not started","summary":"AltID is Denmark's national digital identity wallet, developed by the Danish Agency for Digital Government and launched on 3 June 2026. The application is eIDAS 2.0-compliant and built by digital identity firm Nine. It works alongside the existing MitID authentication system and is available to any Danish resident over the age of 13 with an active MitID account and a Danish CPR number. AltID is designed with a privacy-first architecture in which credentials are stored locally on the user's device rather than in a centralised government database, preventing issuers and service providers from tracking credential usage. Selective disclosure is supported via zero-knowledge proofs, enabling users to confirm age or identity without revealing underlying personal data such as their CPR number or exact date of birth. At launch the wallet supports a digital ID document and an age certificate; additional credentials from public authorities and private organisations are expected in subsequent updates. AltID is Denmark's designated EUDI Wallet implementation in accordance with the eIDAS 2.0 regulation and is designed to be interoperable across the European Union.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"97% > 15 (5,6M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High, eIDAS Substantial, eIDAS Low","name":"MitID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mitid.dk","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"GA","summary":"MitID is Denmark's national digital identity solution, launched in 2021 as the successor to NemID. It enables Danish citizens and residents to authenticate via a smartphone application or hardware token using QR code or code display. MitID is required for banking, government services, and KYC onboarding in Denmark. The service supports three levels of assurance: Low when authenticating with a username and password only; Substantial when using two different authentication factors such as a code display or app confirmation; and High when using the MitID chip app with biometric verification.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Denmark"},{"code":"DO","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2019","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://jce.gob.do","status":"Not started","summary":"The Dominican Republic's national identity card (Cédula de Identidad y Electoral) is issued by the Central Electoral Board (JCE). A digital verification service is available via the JCE portal and mobile application, enabling citizens to access government services. The system covers all Dominican citizens aged 18 and above. Third-party digital identity integration pathways are at an early stage of development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Dominican Republic"},{"code":"EC","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.registrocivil.gob.ec","status":"Not started","summary":"Ecuador's national identity card (Cédula de Ciudadanía) is issued by the Civil Registry (Registro Civil). A digital verification service exists via the government's Tu Identidad platform, enabling institutions to verify identity data against the civil registry. Ecuador is in the early stages of developing a consumer-facing digital identity application. The civil registry database covers all Ecuadorian citizens and residents.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Ecuador"},{"code":"EE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Estonia EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.ria.ee/en/news/eudi-wallet","status":"Not started","summary":"Estonia's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Information System Authority (RIA). A publicly announced project exists, though no public sandbox is yet available for ecosystem participants. Estonia's world-leading digital identity infrastructure — encompassing the eID card, Mobile-ID, and Smart-ID — provides an exceptionally strong foundation for EUDI Wallet compliance. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2002","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Estonian ID-card","officialDocUrl":"https://www.id.ee","status":"Not started","summary":"The Estonian ID-card is the primary mandatory identity document for Estonian citizens and EU/EEA residents permanently residing in Estonia, issued by the Police and Border Guard Board. The card incorporates a smart chip enabling digital authentication and qualified electronic signatures legally equivalent to handwritten signatures. It is the foundational instrument of Estonia's digital society and has been mandatory by law since 2002. As of March 2025, approximately 1.4 million valid ID-cards are in circulation. The card enables access to virtually all Estonian e-services including e-banking, e-tax, e-voting, e-health, and e-prescriptions. Authentication and signing require a compatible card reader and desktop software. The Estonian ID-card is notified under eIDAS at High level of assurance and its digital signatures are recognised across all EU member states.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 18% (230k out of 1,3M) Lithuania: 17% (465k out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2007","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Mobile-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mobiil-id.ee","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Contracting","summary":"Mobile-ID is a SIM-based digital identity solution available in Estonia and Lithuania, operated in conjunction with local telecom providers. Authentication is performed using a dedicated Mobile-ID SIM card issued by the user's telecom operator. The service requires a specifically provisioned SIM, distinguishing it from app-based alternatives such as Smart-ID.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 60% (0,77M out of 1,3M) Latvia: 55% (1M out of 1,8M) Lithuania: 63% (1,75M out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Smart-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.smart-id.com","status":"Contracting","summary":"Smart-ID is a mobile-based digital identity solution widely used across the Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania, and also available in Belgium, operated by SK ID Solutions. Authentication is performed via the Smart-ID application using a personal PIN. The service is available at Basic and Qualified levels; both levels support eIDAS High level of assurance. Smart-ID is widely adopted as an alternative or complement to SIM-based Mobile-ID across the Baltic states.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Estonia"},{"code":"EG","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"National ID (Bitaqat al-Raqm al-Qawmi)","officialDocUrl":"https://digital.gov.eg","status":"Not started","summary":"Egypt's national identity card, known as the National ID (Bitaqat al-Raqm al-Qawmi), is issued by the Civil Status Organisation under the Ministry of Interior. The card incorporates biometric data and is mandatory for all Egyptian citizens aged 16 and above. A digital verification service is available via the government's Digital Egypt portal (eGov), enabling citizens to access public services online. Egypt is developing its digital identity infrastructure as part of its Digital Egypt 2030 national transformation strategy. Third-party private sector integration capabilities are at an early stage of development.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Egypt"},{"code":"ES","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"50% (20 out of 41M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address","Social Security Number","Phone","Email Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2015","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Cl@ve","officialDocUrl":"https://www.clave.gob.es","status":"In Development","summary":"Cl@ve is Spain's national authentication framework for accessing government services, operated by the General State Administration. The system supports two-factor authentication via SMS or a dedicated application. Access to official government data is subject to explicit user consent at each interaction. Phone number and email address returned by the system reflect values self-declared by the user at registration and are not independently verified by the government.","useCases":["IDV"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"21% (6M out of 28M with DL)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","License Class","Document Expiry Date","Document Issue Date","Driver Points"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2020","name":"miDGT","officialDocUrl":"https://www.dgt.es","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"Spain's official driving licence record is administered by the Dirección General de Tráfico (DGT), the national road traffic authority. The service provides access to comprehensive identity and licence information upon explicit user consent, which is required at each verification.","useCases":["IDV","Right to Drive"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Spain EUDI Wallet (Cartera Digital Beta)","officialDocUrl":"https://digital.gob.es","status":"Not started","summary":"Spain's national EUDI Wallet, known as the Cartera Digital Beta, is under development by the Secretary of State for Digitalisation and Artificial Intelligence (SEDIA). Spain has been an active participant in EUDI Wallet pilot programmes and has published developer-facing materials to support ecosystem readiness. The full launch is targeted for December 2026, building on Spain's existing Cl@ve digital identity infrastructure and prior experience in large-scale digital identity deployments.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Spain"},{"code":"FI","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Finland EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://dvv.fi/en/eudi-wallet","status":"Not started","summary":"Finland's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Digital and Population Data Services Agency (DVV), with coordination provided by the Ministry of Finance. A public GitHub repository is available for ecosystem participants. Finland's strong existing digital identity infrastructure — anchored by the Finnish Trust Network — provides a solid foundation for the EUDI Wallet rollout. The wallet is expected to be available by the end of 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"93% (4,3M out of 4,6M > 18)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Finnish Bank ID (Finnish Trust Network)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.tieke.fi/ftn","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Contracting","summary":"The Finnish Trust Network (FTN) is Finland's federated digital identity system, operated by a consortium of Finnish banks and telecommunications providers including Nordea, OP, S-Pankki, Aktia, DNA, and Telia. Also referred to as Finnish Bank ID or Tupas, the network is the primary mechanism for strong authentication in Finnish digital services.","useCases":["IDV","AML","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Finland"},{"code":"FR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","estimatedCoverage":"~4M+ users (~7% of French adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial, eIDAS High","name":"France Identité","officialDocUrl":"https://www.france-identite.gouv.fr","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"Not started","summary":"France Identité is France's national digital identity application, developed by France Titres (the national secure documents agency) under the Ministry of the Interior. The app enables French citizens of legal age holding a credit card format national identity card to create a digital identity, access public services via FranceConnect, import their driver's licence with full legal equivalence, generate single-use proof of identity credentials, and present their identity in person. As of March 2026, over 4 million digital identities have been created, including 750,000 at eIDAS High level of assurance following in-person town hall verification. Over 1.1 million digital driving licences have been issued. France Identité has been designated by the European Commission as France's EUDI Wallet implementation, with the app approved for boarding at all domestic airports from summer 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"15% (8.5M out of 56M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Gender","Birth Place","Email Address","Phone"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"L'Identité Numérique La Poste","officialDocUrl":"https://www.franceconnect.gouv.fr","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"L'Identité Numérique La Poste is France's government-backed digital identity service, operated by La Poste (the French national postal service) via the FranceConnect+ federation. It is distinguished from other FranceConnect providers by a mandatory in-person identity verification step, carried out at a post office or via home delivery by a postal agent, which elevates its level of assurance above other federation members. The service is increasingly relevant in the context of EU age assurance regulations and the forthcoming EUDI Wallet mandate.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"France"},{"code":"GB","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"50% (3,2M out of 6.5M of non-UK nationals)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Portrait","Nationality","Immigration Status"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"UK DIATF Medium Confidence","name":"eVisa (ShareCode)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.uk/view-right-to-work","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"GA","summary":"UK ShareCodes are nine-character alphanumeric codes that link a non-UK or non-Irish national to their UK immigration record (eVisa). They replaced physical Biometric Residence Permits (BRPs), which expired on 31 December 2024. ShareCodes are the primary mechanism for employers and landlords to verify right to work and right to rent for non-UK and non-Irish nationals via the UK Home Office official API. This solution covers approximately 6–7 million non-UK nationals and does not constitute a whole-population eID.","useCases":["Right to Work","IDV"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"23%(13.2M out of 56,6M >18 )","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"UK DIATF Medium Confidence, UK DIATF High Confidence","name":"GOV.UK One Login","officialDocUrl":"https://www.sign-in.service.gov.uk","status":"Researching","summary":"GOV.UK One Login is the UK government's central digital identity and authentication service, operated by the Government Digital Service (GDS). Identity verification is performed using a UK passport or driving licence in combination with facial recognition technology, available via web or the GOV.UK ID Check application. The service is designed to become the standard digital identity solution across all UK government services. As of 2025, the service operates at two confidence levels depending on the document used: High Confidence for passport-based flows and Medium Confidence for driving licence flows.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"93% (50M out of 53,5M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2020","levelOfAssurance":"UK DIATF Medium Confidence","name":"OneID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.oneid.uk","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"GA","summary":"OneID is a UK bank-backed digital identity service that enables users to verify their identity using existing online banking credentials, with no application download required. Participating banks include Barclays, Lloyds, NatWest, HSBC, and Santander and many others.","useCases":["IDV"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"7% (5M out of 69,3M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Document Expiry Date"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2022","levelOfAssurance":"UK DIATF Medium Confidence","name":"UK PASS Card Verification","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/document-checking-service","status":"Contracting","summary":"The UK PASS (Proof of Age Standards Scheme) card scheme is a government-backed accreditation framework that certifies identity and proof-of-age cards issued by approved providers, offering a trusted alternative to passports and driving licences. PASS cards display the PASS hologram and are widely accepted across the UK for age-restricted purchases and identity verification purposes.","useCases":["IDV"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"United Kingdom"},{"code":"GE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (card) / In Development (eID)","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Georgia eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mia.gov.ge","status":"Not started","summary":"Georgia's national eID card, issued by the Civil Registry Agency of the Ministry of Justice, serves as the primary instrument for citizen identification and incorporates a chip enabling digital authentication for government services. Georgia was granted EU candidate status in December 2023 and has participated in the EU4Digital cross-border eID pilot programme, which supports digital identity interoperability between Eastern Partnership countries and the European Union. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels, with broader integration capabilities under active development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Georgia"},{"code":"GH","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~17M+ enrolled (~52% of Ghanaian population)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Ghana Card","officialDocUrl":"https://www.nia.gov.gh","status":"Not started","summary":"The Ghana Card is Ghana's national biometric identity card, issued by the National Identification Authority (NIA) to all Ghanaian citizens and foreign residents. The card incorporates a microchip storing biometric data including fingerprints and a facial image, and is widely regarded as one of the most advanced digital identity systems on the African continent. The Ghana Card is mandatory for tax filing, banking, and voter registration, and is increasingly recognised as a travel document for regional movement within ECOWAS. Digital verification is available via the NIA's GhanaPostGPS-integrated platform.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Ghana"},{"code":"GR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2022","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Gov.gr Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.wallet.gov.gr","status":"Not started","summary":"Gov.gr Wallet is Greece's national digital identity wallet, available on Android and iOS. It enables Greek citizens to store and present digital versions of their national identity card, driver's licence, and other official documents, all of which carry full legal equivalence to their physical counterparts. The Gov.gr Wallet is designated as Greece's EUDI Wallet implementation, with an upgrade to full eIDAS 2.0 compliance confirmed by the Ministry of Digital Governance. Greece is classified among the more advanced EU member states in terms of EUDI Wallet preparation given its existing live wallet infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Greece"},{"code":"HR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Croatia EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://gov.hr","status":"Not started","summary":"Croatia's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Ministry of Justice and Digital Transformation. A publicly announced project exists, though no public sandbox is yet available. Croatia is expected to meet the December 2026 deadline, with the existing eOsobna national eID card infrastructure serving as a foundation for the wallet rollout.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Croatian eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.hr","status":"Not started","summary":"Croatia's national electronic identity is based on the eOsobna digital identity card, which incorporates an NFC chip. The card is used for accessing government services. No standalone consumer-facing digital identity application is currently available for third-party integration. Croatia is developing its digital identity infrastructure in alignment with the EUDI Wallet mandate.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Croatia"},{"code":"HU","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"DÁP Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.dap.gov.hu","status":"Not started","summary":"The DÁP Wallet (Digitális Állampolgárság Program) is Hungary's national digital identity wallet, operated by the Ministry of the Interior. It provides digital representations of official national documents and is available via a dedicated application. Hungary's national ID cards are NFC-enabled, supporting chip-based verification. The DÁP Wallet is designated as Hungary's EUDI Wallet implementation and is targeting full eIDAS 2.0 compliance by December 2026, with an upgrade of the existing app confirmed by the Hungarian government.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Hungary"},{"code":"ID","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"6.5% of population","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Age","Gender"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2022 Pilot 2024 Formal Public implementation","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"IKD","officialDocUrl":"https://dukcapil.kemendagri.go.id/","status":"Researching","summary":"e-KTP (Kartu Tanda Penduduk Elektronik) is Indonesia's national electronic identity card, issued to citizens aged 17 and above by the Directorate General of Population and Civil Registration (Dukcapil) under the Ministry of Home Affairs. The card uses contactless smart card technology with an embedded microchip storing biometric data like fingerprints and a digital photograph — alongside a unique 16-digit National Identity Number (NIK), which serves as the primary identifier across government and financial services. Verification against Dukcapil's national population database is available to authorised institutions. Indonesia is in active transition toward a fully digital successor: the IKD (Identitas Kependudukan Digital), a smartphone-based digital identity that encodes the e-KTP into a QR code format, with the government targeting complete migration away from physical card blanks. Adoption of IKD has progressed unevenly, with challenges in rural connectivity and digital literacy slowing uptake outside urban centres.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Indonesia"},{"code":"IE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Ireland EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.ie/en/press-release/d8ee9-ireland-opens-access-to-digital-wallet-project/","status":"Not started","summary":"Ireland's national EUDI Wallet, referred to as the Government Digital Wallet, is under development by the Irish Government. A public sandbox launched in early 2026, enabling ecosystem participants to begin integration testing ahead of the production launch. Ireland has completed a 500-person civil servant pilot programme and is in the process of drafting legislation to provide digital credentials with full legal status. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026, operating in parallel with the existing MyGovID service.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Social Security Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"MyGovID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mygovid.ie","status":"Not started","summary":"MyGovID is Ireland's government digital identity application, operated by the Department of Public Expenditure and Reform. It enables users to verify their identity and access public services using their Public Services Card (PSC). Use of MyGovID is not mandatory, and the application is available on iOS and Android with rollout ongoing. Ireland is separately developing a dedicated EUDI Wallet implementation in parallel with the MyGovID service.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Ireland"},{"code":"IN","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"99.9% of Indian adults","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait","Address","Gender"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2010 (first issued) / 2016 (Aadhaar Act)","levelOfAssurance":"IN UIDAI High","name":"Aadhaar (via DigiLocker)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.uidai.gov.in","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"GA","summary":"Aadhaar is India's biometric-backed national identity system, operated by the Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI). It assigns a unique 12-digit identifier to every Indian resident and constitutes one of the largest digital identity systems in the world. Third-party access is facilitated via DigiLocker, as private sector entities cannot integrate with Aadhaar directly. Verification returns a match or no-match result; no personally identifiable information is stored by the verifying party. Authentication requires an Indian phone number linked to the Aadhaar record and an active SIM for OTP delivery. As of December 2025, newly issued Aadhaar cards no longer display the number or name; verification is QR code-based only, with a transition deadline of 14 June 2026.","useCases":["IDV","AML","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"India"},{"code":"IQ","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"National ID (Bitaqat al-Hawية al-Wataniya)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.moi.gov.iq","status":"Not started","summary":"Iraq's national identity card is issued by the Directorate of Nationality under the Ministry of Interior. A national biometric identity card programme was launched with UNAMI and international support to replace older identification documents. Digital government services remain limited due to ongoing infrastructure development. Third-party digital identity integration is not currently available.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Iraq"},{"code":"IS","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2020","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Auðkennisappið","officialDocUrl":"https://www.audkenni.is","status":"Not started","summary":"Auðkennisappið is Iceland's national electronic identity application, developed by Auðkenni hf. and used by Icelandic citizens and residents for authentication across banking, government, and private sector services. Unlike SIM-based electronic identity schemes, the app is not dependent on an Icelandic phone number or SIM card, making it accessible to Icelanders abroad and residents with foreign phone numbers. Registration requires a valid Icelandic passport and is performed via self-service or at an authorised enrolment centre. Approximately 97% of the eligible Icelandic population holds an active eID, including 75% of those aged over 75. The app supports both authentication and electronic document signing, with signatures carrying legal equivalence to handwritten signatures.","useCases":["IDV","Authentication","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2027 (expected)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Iceland EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://island.is","status":"Not started","summary":"Iceland's national EUDI Wallet is under development as part of its obligations as a member of the European Economic Area (EEA). As a non-EU EEA member, Iceland benefits from an extended implementation deadline of December 2027. Iceland is actively participating in the EUDI Wallet pilot programme and the wallet is expected to build on the existing Icelandic eID Card infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Icelandic eID Card","officialDocUrl":"https://www.island.is","status":"Not started","summary":"Iceland's electronic national identity card was released in March 2024, making it among the first of its kind to feature a portrait card orientation and an NFC chip for digital authentication. Iceland is participating in the EUDI Wallet pilot programme as a member of the European Economic Area (EEA). As a non-EU EEA member, Iceland is subject to eIDAS compliance requirements and has an extended EUDI Wallet implementation deadline of December 2027.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Iceland"},{"code":"IT","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"9M with active digital credentials (CieID) (16%)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address","Nationality","Tax ID"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High, eIDAS Substantial, eIDAS Low","name":"CIE (Carta d'Identità Elettronica)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.cartaidentita.interno.gov.it","status":"Not started","summary":"The Carta d'Identità Elettronica (CIE) is Italy's national electronic identity card, issued by the Ministry of the Interior via municipal offices. The card incorporates an NFC-enabled microchip storing biometric data and enables digital authentication for government and private sector services via the CieID app and CIE 3.0 infrastructure. As of August 3, 2026, the CIE fully replaces the old paper identity card for all purposes including travel within the European Union. Approximately 48 million CIEs have been issued as of early 2025, making it the most widely held digital identity credential in Italy. The CIE is the authentication mechanism used to activate IT Wallet credentials and is progressively replacing SPID as Italy's primary digital identity standard. The service supports three levels of assurance: Low when authenticating with username and password only, Substantial when using credentials with an OTP code, and High when using the CieID app or a card reader with NFC. The CIE is designated as the foundational credential for Italy's EUDI Wallet ecosystem, with full eIDAS 2.0 interoperability targeted for December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Authentication","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~10M+ activations (~17% of Italian adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Tax ID","License Number","Portrait"],"idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Italy EUDI Wallet (IT Wallet)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.io.italia.it","status":"Not started","summary":"IT Wallet is Italy's national digital identity wallet, integrated into the IO app operated by PagoPA under the Department of Digital Transformation. It enables Italian citizens to store and present digital versions of key documents including their driving licence, health card, and European Disability Card, with full legal equivalence to their physical counterparts. The wallet pilot launched in October 2024 with 50,000 selected users, expanding in phases through November 2024, and became available to all Italian citizens and residents from 4 December 2024. As of early 2026, IT Wallet had surpassed 10 million activations, with over 17.3 million digital documents stored. IT Wallet uses the CIE or SPID for initial identity verification and onboarding. Italy has designated IT Wallet as its EUDI Wallet implementation, with full eIDAS 2.0 alignment and EU interoperability required by December 2026. By end of 2026, the wallet is expected to support over 200 digital document types.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"83% (41,5M out of 50,5M >18)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Gender","Birth Place","Email Address","Phone"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"SPID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.spid.gov.it","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"SPID (Sistema Pubblico di Identità Digitale) is Italy's public digital identity system, providing a standardised authentication mechanism for accessing public and private digital services. SPID is gradually being complemented by the IT Wallet and CIE (Carta d'Identità Elettronica) as part of Italy's long-term digital identity infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Italy"},{"code":"JO","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"National ID (Hawية الجنسية)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.moi.gov.jo","status":"Not started","summary":"Jordan's national identity card is issued by the Civil Status and Passports Department (CSPD) under the Ministry of Interior. The card incorporates biometric data and a chip, and is mandatory for all Jordanian citizens aged 16 and above. A digital government portal (Jordan e-Government) provides online access to identity verification services for public services. Jordan has one of the more advanced digital government ecosystems in the Middle East, with the Ministry of Digital Economy and Entrepreneurship coordinating national digital transformation efforts.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Jordan"},{"code":"JP","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~100M+ cards issued (~80% of Japanese population)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"My Number Card","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digital.go.jp/en/policies/mynumber","status":"Not started","summary":"My Number Card (マイナンバーカード) is Japan's national digital identity card, managed by the Digital Agency of Japan and the Japan Agency for Local Authority Information Systems. The card incorporates an IC chip enabling digital authentication for government and private sector services. As of late 2025, over 100 million cards have been issued, covering approximately 80% of the Japanese population. The card has replaced physical health insurance cards as of December 2024, following a government mandate requiring all health insurance beneficiaries to register their My Number Card. From March 2025, the card additionally functions as a driver's licence, with licence information stored on the IC chip. The card can be loaded into Apple Wallet on iPhone for digital presentation. Japan is developing a mobile driver's licence aligned with the ISO 18013-5 standard, with no confirmed launch date.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Japan"},{"code":"KE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Maisha Namba","officialDocUrl":"https://usajili.go.ke","status":"Not started","summary":"Kenya's national digital identity system is currently transitioning from the previous Huduma Namba programme (which was declared partially unconstitutional in 2021) to a new Unique Personal Identifier (UPI) known as Maisha Namba, administered by the National Registration Bureau. The new system is designed to register births and deaths and serve as a lifelong digital identity for accessing government services including the Kenya Revenue Authority, NHIF, and NSSF. The transition is ongoing, with legal and technical frameworks continuing to be refined under the Data Protection Act.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Kenya"},{"code":"KR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2025","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Mobile Resident Registration Card","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mois.go.kr","status":"Not started","summary":"South Korea's mobile resident registration card is a digital version of the national identity card, available via the Mobile IDentification app operated by the Ministry of the Interior and Safety. Launched in March 2025, it is available to all citizens aged 17 and above, as well as foreign residents aged 14 and above via a digital residence card. Users register by completing NFC verification of their physical chip-enabled card or by scanning a QR code at a community centre. Biometric verification is required and each digital ID is bound to a single registered smartphone. Digital documents carry the same legal validity as their physical counterparts. The system is integrated with 15 major Korean banks, enabling citizens to open accounts and access financial services using their mobile credentials. Note: South Korea's digital ID system uses a domestic credential format that is not currently compatible with international standards such as ISO 18013-5 or SD-JWT+VC, which may limit cross-border interoperability.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","KYC"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~30M+ registered users (~58% of South Korean adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Phone","License Number","Portrait","Age Verification"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2018","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"PASS","officialDocUrl":"https://www.passauth.co.kr","status":"Not started","summary":"PASS is South Korea's telecom-backed digital identity and authentication application, developed by SK Telecom, KT, and LG Uplus in collaboration with the Korean National Police Agency. Launched in 2018 for mobile financial authentication, the app was extended in 2020 to include a digital driver's licence, legally equivalent to the physical card, verified in real time against the National Police Agency and Korea Road Traffic Authority systems. The digital licence displays the user's photo alongside a dynamically refreshed QR code and barcode to prevent fraud. Each digital licence is bound to a single smartphone registered under the user's name. PASS is used across convenience stores, hospitals, financial institutions, and government services for identity and age verification. As of 2025 the app has over 30 million registered users, making it one of the most widely adopted digital identity applications in South Korea.","useCases":["IDV","Authentication","Age Verification"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"South Korea"},{"code":"KW","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Civil ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.paci.gov.kw","status":"Not started","summary":"Kuwait's Civil ID is managed by the Public Authority for Civil Information (PACI) and is mandatory for all citizens and residents. The PACI-issued smart card incorporates PKI key pairs and biometric fingerprint templates. In 2024, Kuwait introduced digital Civil ID renewal functionality via the Sahel government application. Digital identity verification is currently accessible through government-operated channels; a dedicated public-facing digital identity application is not yet available.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Kuwait"},{"code":"LI","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2019","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"eID.li","officialDocUrl":"https://www.eid.li","status":"Not started","summary":"eID.li is Liechtenstein's national mobile eID application, operated by the government. It enables citizens to authenticate digitally and present official identity documents via smartphone. The application is notified under eIDAS and is available on iOS and Android. As a non-EU EEA member, Liechtenstein is subject to eIDAS compliance requirements and has an extended EUDI Wallet implementation deadline of December 2027.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2027 (expected)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Liechtenstein EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.llv.li","status":"Not started","summary":"Liechtenstein's national EUDI Wallet is under development as part of its obligations as a member of the European Economic Area (EEA). As a non-EU EEA member, Liechtenstein benefits from an extended implementation deadline of December 2027. The wallet is expected to build on the existing eID.li infrastructure. Liechtenstein is a small jurisdiction with a population of approximately 39,000 and well-established digital identity foundations.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Liechtenstein"},{"code":"LT","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Lithuania EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.ivpk.lrv.lt","status":"Not started","summary":"Lithuania's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Informatics and Communications Department under the Ministry of the Interior. Active procurement and testbed-related work are underway, though no public sandbox is yet available. Lithuania's experience with Smart-ID and Mobile-ID adoption across the Baltic states provides relevant context for the wallet's development. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 18% (230k out of 1,3M) Lithuania: 17% (465k out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2007","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Mobile-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mobiil-id.ee","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Contracting","summary":"Mobile-ID is a SIM-based digital identity solution available in Estonia and Lithuania, operated in conjunction with local telecom providers. Authentication is performed using a dedicated Mobile-ID SIM card issued by the user's telecom operator. The service requires a specifically provisioned SIM, distinguishing it from app-based alternatives such as Smart-ID.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 60% (0,77M out of 1,3M) Latvia: 55% (1M out of 1,8M) Lithuania: 63% (1,75M out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Smart-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.smart-id.com","status":"Contracting","summary":"Smart-ID is a mobile-based digital identity solution widely used across the Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania, and also available in Belgium, operated by SK ID Solutions. Authentication is performed via the Smart-ID application using a personal PIN. The service is available at Basic and Qualified levels; both levels support eIDAS High level of assurance. Smart-ID is widely adopted as an alternative or complement to SIM-based Mobile-ID across the Baltic states.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Lithuania"},{"code":"LU","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Email Address"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"itsme Basic","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"itsme Basic is a lightweight authentication variant of the itsme platform that confirms a user's identity based on their existing itsme account, without requiring a full document-based identity verification process such as NFC chip scanning. The service returns minimal identity data comprising name and email address.","useCases":["Authentication","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"itsme Standard","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","status":"GA","summary":"itsme is a bank- and telecom-backed digital identity application operated by the Belgian Mobile ID consortium. Identity verification is performed by scanning the NFC chip of a physical ID card or passport via the itsme app, followed by PIN or biometric authentication. The service is available in Belgium, Luxembourg, and the Netherlands, and is widely adopted for regulated onboarding across financial services and age-restricted platforms.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Luxembourg EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://luxembourg.lu/en/digital-luxembourg/digital-identity/","status":"Not started","summary":"Luxembourg's national EUDI Wallet implementation is based on a confirmed upgrade of the existing LuxTrust infrastructure, endorsed by the Ministry for Digitalisation. Luxembourg is considered one of the better-prepared EU member states, with a clear upgrade pathway from an established and widely adopted existing service. Full EUDI Wallet compliance is targeted for December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2011","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"LuxTrust","officialDocUrl":"https://www.luxtrust.com","status":"Not started","summary":"LuxTrust is Luxembourg's national digital identity and qualified electronic signature service. It is widely used for banking and government services across Luxembourg and provides eIDAS Substantial level of assurance. The service supports both certificate-based authentication via smart card and mobile-based authentication via the LuxTrust Mobile application.","useCases":["IDV","Digital Signing","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Luxembourg"},{"code":"LV","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"36% (555k out of 1,55M > 14)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2011","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High, eIDAS Substantial","name":"Latvia eParaksts","officialDocUrl":"https://www.eparaksts.lv","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Researching","summary":"eParaksts is Latvia's national digital signature and authentication system, operated by the Latvian State Radio and Television Centre (LVRTC). It is available in two forms: eParaksts Mobile, a smartphone application, and eParaksts Smart Card, which requires a physical smart card reader. The service enables Latvian citizens to authenticate digitally and sign documents with legal equivalence to handwritten signatures. The service supports two levels of assurance: eIDAS High when using a hardware keystore on a certified device, and eIDAS Substantial when using a software keystore.","useCases":["IDV","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Latvia EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.varam.gov.lv/en/eudi-wallet","status":"Not started","summary":"Latvia's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the State Digital Development Agency (LVRTC). A publicly announced project exists, though no public sandbox is yet available for ecosystem testing. Latvia's existing eParaksts digital signature and authentication infrastructure provides a strong technical foundation for the EUDI Wallet rollout. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"Estonia: 60% (0,77M out of 1,3M) Latvia: 55% (1M out of 1,8M) Lithuania: 63% (1,75M out of 2,8M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Smart-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.smart-id.com","status":"Contracting","summary":"Smart-ID is a mobile-based digital identity solution widely used across the Baltic states of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania, and also available in Belgium, operated by SK ID Solutions. Authentication is performed via the Smart-ID application using a personal PIN. The service is available at Basic and Qualified levels; both levels support eIDAS High level of assurance. Smart-ID is widely adopted as an alternative or complement to SIM-based Mobile-ID across the Baltic states.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Latvia"},{"code":"MA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"CIN (Carte d'Identité Nationale)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.idarati.ma","status":"Not started","summary":"Morocco's national identity card (Carte d'Identité Nationale — CIN) is issued by the General Directorate of National Security (DGSN). The card incorporates biometric data and an electronic chip. Morocco launched a digital identity programme as part of its Digital Morocco 2030 strategy, with a government e-services portal (idarati.ma) providing online access to administrative services. Third-party digital identity integration for private sector use cases is at an early stage of development, though Morocco has one of the more advanced digital government ecosystems in North Africa.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Morocco"},{"code":"MC","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Monaco Digital ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gouv.mc","status":"Not started","summary":"Since 28 June 2021, all Monaco citizens and residents are eligible to obtain a digital identity linked to their national identity card, deployed by IN Groupe, the French national secure printing authority. The digital identity is embedded within the physical card via an NFC chip. Monaco is a small jurisdiction with a population of approximately 38,000 and maintains close institutional ties with France, though it is not an EU member state.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Monaco"},{"code":"MD","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"MPass / Moldova eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mpass.md","status":"Not started","summary":"Moldova's digital identity infrastructure comprises two complementary systems. MPass, operational since 2014, is Moldova's national mobile signature and authentication system. The EVO application serves as Moldova's national public services platform and houses the digital identity wallet module, with EVOSign providing electronic signature functionality. In May 2026, Moldova launched a new digital eID card aligned with eIDAS standards. As an EU candidate country since 2022, Moldova joined the WE BUILD consortium, one of the European Commission's large-scale EUDI Wallet pilot programmes, and is among the most advanced non-EU countries in aligning its digital identity infrastructure with European standards.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Moldova"},{"code":"ME","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Montenegro eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.me","status":"Not started","summary":"Montenegro's national identity infrastructure is based on a biometric smart ID card, issued by the Ministry of Interior, which incorporates an NFC chip enabling digital authentication. The eGovernment portal provides citizens with online access to public services. Montenegro is among the most advanced Western Balkan countries in the EU accession process, and digital identity development is proceeding in alignment with EU standards. Broader digital identity integration capabilities are currently under development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Montenegro"},{"code":"MK","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"North Macedonia eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.uslugi.gov.mk","status":"Not started","summary":"North Macedonia's national identity infrastructure comprises a biometric identity card, issued by the Ministry of Interior, and an eGovernment portal that enables citizens to access public services online. North Macedonia is an EU accession candidate and has demonstrated sound digital preparedness according to OECD 2025 assessments. Digital identity development is proceeding in alignment with EU standards, with broader integration capabilities under development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"North Macedonia"},{"code":"MT","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","name":"Malta EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mdia.gov.mt","status":"Not started","summary":"The Maltese Digital Wallet is Malta's national digital identity wallet, under development by the Malta Digital Innovation Authority (MDIA). No consumer-facing application is currently available for third-party integration. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026, in compliance with the EUDI Wallet mandate, though initial functionality at launch is expected to be limited. Full feature compliance is anticipated post-launch.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Malta"},{"code":"MX","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"CURP Biométrica (PUI)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gob.mx/segob/renapo","status":"Not started","summary":"Mexico's national digital identity system is anchored to the Clave Única de Registro de Población (CURP), an 18-character alphanumeric code assigned to all citizens and legal residents. Following legislative reforms published in July 2025, the CURP was upgraded to incorporate biometric data (fingerprints, iris scans, and photograph) and became a mandatory official identification document for all residents from January 2026. The new Plataforma Única de Identidad (PUI) combines CURP biometric records with other administrative data and is integrated with the Llave MX secure authentication platform. The system is mandatory for access to public services including banking, healthcare, education, and social programmes, as well as for SIM card registration from 2026. A phased national rollout is underway through 2028, with implementation varying by state.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Mexico"},{"code":"MY","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"30% of population","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024 Public Release","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"MyDigitalID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digital-id.my/en","status":"Researching","summary":"MyDigitalID is Malaysia's national digital identity platform, developed by My Digital ID Sdn Bhd and functioning as the digital extension of MyKad, the country's physical national identity card. It operates as a single sign-on (SSO) system, verifying identities against the National Registration Department database in real time without storing personal data on the platform itself. Registration requires users to submit their MyKad number, a photo of the physical card, and a selfie for biometric matching. The platform is currently restricted to Malaysian citizens; foreign nationals are not yet in scope. Adoption is being driven through mandatory integration: from December 2025, all telecommunications operators are required to use MyDigitalID for SIM registration, and from January 2026, it became the sole login method for the government's immigration application MyNIISe. While sign-up is not yet legally compulsory, the government has begun auto-pre-registering Malaysians from age 12 via the National Registration Department to accelerate coverage.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Malaysia"},{"code":"NG","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~68.6M registered (~33% of Nigerian population)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2014","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"BVN (Bank Verification Number)","officialDocUrl":"https://nibss-plc.com.ng/bank-verification-numberbvn/","status":"Not started","summary":"The Bank Verification Number (BVN) is Nigeria's bank-backed biometric identity system, operated by the Nigeria Inter-Bank Settlement System (NIBSS) under the mandate of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN). Introduced in 2014, the BVN assigns a unique 11-digit identifier to each bank customer, linked to biometric data including all ten fingerprints and a facial image. The BVN is mandatory for operating a bank account in Nigeria and is increasingly required for access to government social programmes, mobile money, and digital lending services. As of Q1 2026, 68.6 million BVNs have been registered. The system functions as a centralised identity layer across the entire Nigerian banking sector, enabling real-time identity verification and fraud prevention. Access to BVN data for third-party verification requires authorisation from NIBSS.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~104M+ enrolled (~50% of Nigerian population)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2012","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"NIN (National Identification Number)","officialDocUrl":"https://nimc.gov.ng","status":"Not started","summary":"The National Identification Number (NIN) is Nigeria's national digital identity system, operated by the National Identity Management Commission (NIMC). Each Nigerian citizen and legal resident is assigned a unique 11-digit NIN linked to biometric data including fingerprints and facial image. The NIN is mandatory for access to a wide range of services including SIM card registration, banking, passport issuance, and social welfare programmes. As of 2025, over 104 million NINs have been enrolled, supported by World Bank and European Investment Bank funding targeting 180 million enrolments. The National Identity Card, which carries the NIN and biometric chip, is the primary physical credential issued by NIMC.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Nigeria"},{"code":"NL","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"83% (13M out of 15,5M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Initials","Date of Birth","Gender"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2016","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"iDIN login","officialDocUrl":"https://www.idin.nl","varianceCoverage":"GA","status":"Open Beta","summary":"iDIN is the Netherlands' bank-backed digital identity service, operated by the Dutch Banking Association (NVB) and managed by itsme following its acquisition. Authentication is performed using existing online banking credentials, requiring no additional registration. The first name field returns initials only rather than the full given name, and the identifier returned is bank-specific rather than a national identity number. The Netherlands has indicated it is unlikely to meet the December 2026 EUDI Wallet deadline and may launch with limited initial functionality. From mid-2026, iDIN will transition to the itsme app; iDIN will remain available for at least two more years, with the transition expected to complete in 2028.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Email Address"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"itsme Basic","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"itsme Basic is a lightweight authentication variant of the itsme platform that confirms a user's identity based on their existing itsme account, without requiring a full document-based identity verification process such as NFC chip scanning. The service returns minimal identity data comprising name and email address.","useCases":["Authentication","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (Belgium), 60% (Luxembourg), 30% (Netherlands)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"itsme Standard","officialDocUrl":"https://www.itsme.be","status":"GA","summary":"itsme is a bank- and telecom-backed digital identity application operated by the Belgian Mobile ID consortium. Identity verification is performed by scanning the NFC chip of a physical ID card or passport via the itsme app, followed by PIN or biometric authentication. The service is available in Belgium, Luxembourg, and the Netherlands, and is widely adopted for regulated onboarding across financial services and age-restricted platforms.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Netherlands EUDI Wallet (NL Wallet)","officialDocUrl":"https://github.com/MinBZK/nl-wallet","status":"Not started","summary":"The NL Wallet is the Netherlands' national EUDI Wallet implementation, developed by the Ministry of the Interior and Kingdom Relations. The project is conducted openly, with a public GitHub repository available for ecosystem participants to follow development progress. The Netherlands has publicly indicated it is unlikely to meet the December 2026 deadline in full and may launch with limited initial functionality, making it one of the higher-risk EU member states for timely delivery. Development builds on the Netherlands' existing digital identity infrastructure.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Netherlands"},{"code":"NO","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2027 (expected)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Norway EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digdir.no/digital-identitet/eu-digital-identity-wallet/5485","status":"Not started","summary":"Norway's national EUDI Wallet is under development as part of its obligations as a member of the European Economic Area (EEA). As a non-EU EEA member, Norway benefits from an extended implementation deadline of December 2027. The Norwegian Digitalisation Agency (Digitaliseringsdirektoratet) is coordinating the implementation, with the existing BankID infrastructure expected to serve as a foundational component of the wallet ecosystem.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"99% (4,6 M users)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2004","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial, eIDAS High","name":"Norwegian BankID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.bankid.no","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"Norwegian BankID is Norway's national bank-backed digital identity solution, operated by a consortium of Norwegian banks. Authentication is performed via one-time code (OTP) or a dedicated mobile application. It is one of the most widely adopted digital identity systems in Europe, with near-universal coverage among Norwegian internet users. The service supports two levels of assurance: eIDAS High when authentication is performed via the BankID mobile application with biometric verification, and eIDAS Substantial when performed via one-time code or hardware token.","useCases":["IDV","AML","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Norway"},{"code":"NZ","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"TBD (Targeted 2025-2026)","name":"mDL/DDL","officialDocUrl":"https://www.nzta.govt.nz/driver-licences","status":"Not started","summary":"A national Digital Driver Licence (DDL) is in development by NZ Transport Agency (Waka Kotahi) alongside other government agencies, with an initial release targeted for late 2025–2026. It will be built to the international ISO/IEC 18013-5 standard and issued under New Zealand's Digital Identity Services Trust Framework (in force from 24 July 2025), accessed through accredited digital wallets rather than a single central database; RealMe remains the country's primary government digital identity in the interim.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"20-25% of NZ population","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"NZ DISTF","name":"RealMe","officialDocUrl":"https://www.realme.govt.nz","status":"Not started","summary":"RealMe is New Zealand's government digital identity service, operated by the Department of Internal Affairs (DIA). It offers two tiers: a \"RealMe login\" single sign-on credential for accessing government services, and \"RealMe verified identity,\" a higher-assurance service that confirms a person's identity against authoritative government records (including passport data) and a biometric selfie. Verified identity is used for regulated onboarding such as banking and KYC, and operates within New Zealand's Digital Identity Services Trust Framework.","useCases":["IDV","AML","Gov't Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"New Zealand"},{"code":"OM","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"National ID / TasHeel","officialDocUrl":"https://www.rop.gov.om","status":"Not started","summary":"Oman's national identity is managed through the Royal Oman Police (ROP). TasHeel is Oman's government services platform, providing citizens and residents with access to official government services. A dedicated consumer-facing digital identity application for third-party integration is not yet available. Digital identity infrastructure is developing as part of the Oman Vision 2040 programme.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Oman"},{"code":"PA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2020","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.tribunal-electoral.gob.pa","status":"Not started","summary":"Panama's national identity card (Cédula de Identidad Personal) is issued by the Electoral Tribunal (Tribunal Electoral). A digital verification service exists via the Electoral Tribunal's portal. Panama's national identity system covers all citizens and permanent residents. Digital identity infrastructure for private sector third-party integration is at an early stage of development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Panama"},{"code":"PE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2013","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"DNIe / RENIEC","officialDocUrl":"https://www.reniec.gob.pe","status":"Not started","summary":"Peru's national electronic identity card (DNIe) is issued by the National Registry of Identification and Civil Status (RENIEC) and has been available since 2013. The card incorporates a microchip compliant with ISO 7816 standards and enables digital authentication and qualified electronic signatures. As of August 2025, Peru has ceased issuing the traditional physical DNI in favour of the electronic version for all new applicants. RENIEC's Ciudadano Digital platform provides a PKI-based infrastructure for digital authentication. The system covers virtually all Peruvian citizens and is accepted as a travel document across Mercosur countries.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Peru"},{"code":"PH","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"80% (90,3M out of 116M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Sex","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"PH PhilSys LoA 2","name":"PhilSys","officialDocUrl":"https://www.verify.philsys.gov.ph","varianceCoverage":"Alpha","status":"Open Beta","summary":"PhilSys is the Philippines' national digital identity system, operated by the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA). Identity verification is performed by scanning the QR code on the physical PhilSys card against the official government verification portal. Over 115 million PhilSys IDs have been issued by the Philippine government, although adoption of the digital QR verification method continues to grow.","useCases":["IDV"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Philippines"},{"code":"PL","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"3% (1M+ out of 32,4M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Document Expiry Date","Sex"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"eDO App","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.pl/edo","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"eDO App is Poland's government digital identity solution, operated by the Polish Security Printing Works (PWPW). Identity verification is performed exclusively by scanning the NFC chip of a Polish e-ID card or biometric passport; no credential-based authentication is supported. The service is available to Polish citizens and residents holding a chip-enabled Polish national ID card or passport.","useCases":["IDV"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~10M active users (~33% of Polish adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2019","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"mObywatel","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mobywatel.gov.pl","status":"Not started","summary":"mObywatel is Poland's national government digital identity application, operated by the Ministry of Digitalisation and developed by the Central IT Centre (COI). It provides citizens with digital versions of their national identity card, driving licence, and other official documents, all legally equivalent to their physical counterparts. Identity verification is based on data extracted from the PESEL national registry. The app has surpassed 10 million active users as of 2025, with over 1 million daily logins, and provides access to over 40 government services. Third-party integration requires formal approval from the Ministry of Digitalisation and the Central IT Centre. Poland is developing mObywatel 3.0 as its designated EUDI Wallet implementation, targeting full eIDAS 2.0 compliance by 2026, while running the current version in parallel to ensure service continuity.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"PL: 68% (22M out of 32,5M > 15) Czechia: 8% (700k out of 9M > 15)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2010","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"MojeID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.mojeid.cz","status":"Contracting","summary":"MojeID is a digital identity system available in Poland and the Czech Republic, enabling users to authenticate via an account with a participating identity provider such as a bank or other registered organisation. The service is widely used for accessing government and private sector digital services in both markets, with significantly higher adoption in Poland than in the Czech Republic. No additional app download or registration beyond an existing account with a participating provider is required.","useCases":["IDV"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Poland"},{"code":"PT","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"93% (9,7M out of 10,4M)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Social Security Number","Address","Email Address","Phone"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Chave Móvel Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.autenticacao.gov.pt","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"Chave Móvel Digital (CMD) is Portugal's national digital authentication system, operated by the Agency for Administrative Modernisation (AMA). It supports both SMS-based and app-based two-factor authentication, enabling citizens to access official government services and share verified identity data from government registries. User consent is required at each verification.","useCases":["IDV"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Portugal EUDI Wallet (gov.pt Wallet)","officialDocUrl":"https://ama.gov.pt","status":"Not started","summary":"Portugal's national EUDI Wallet, referred to as the gov.pt Wallet, is under development by the Agency for Administrative Modernisation (AMA). While a formal confirmation of the upgrade pathway from the existing Chave Móvel Digital infrastructure has not yet been published, Portugal is expected to meet the December 2026 deadline. Integration details and the technical architecture for the wallet remain in active development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Portugal"},{"code":"QA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"QDI (Qatar Digital Identity)","officialDocUrl":"https://www.moi.gov.qa","status":"Not started","summary":"QDI (Qatar Digital Identity) is Qatar's national digital identity wallet, launched in October 2024 by the Ministry of Interior. It provides digital representations of the Qatar ID (QID), passport, and driver's licence. The initiative forms part of Qatar's National Digital Authentication and Trust Services Strategy 2024–2026. The service is in an early adoption phase, with coverage growing and integration pathways for private sector organisations under development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Qatar"},{"code":"RO","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"ROeID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.ghiseul.ro","status":"Not started","summary":"ROeID is Romania's national digital identity scheme, pre-notified under the eIDAS regulation. It enables Romanian citizens to authenticate digitally to government services. The scheme is currently available for government service access, with broader interoperability and private sector integration under development.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Romania EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://ghiseul.ro","status":"Not started","summary":"Romania's national EUDI Wallet is under development, building on the existing ROeID digital identity infrastructure. A publicly announced project exists, though no public sandbox is yet available for ecosystem testing. The ROeID pre-notification under eIDAS provides a regulatory foundation for the EUDI Wallet rollout. Romania is expected to meet the December 2026 deadline.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Romania"},{"code":"RS","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (card) / In Development (eID)","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Serbian eID / eUprava","officialDocUrl":"https://www.euprava.gov.rs","status":"Not started","summary":"Serbia's digital identity infrastructure comprises a biometric smart card national eID and the eUprava eGovernment portal, which provides citizens with online access to public services. As an EU candidate country, Serbia is developing its digital identity services in alignment with EU standards. The physical identity card is well established and widely held; digital identity services are accessible primarily through government-operated channels, with broader interoperability under development as part of the EU accession process.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Serbia"},{"code":"RU","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"100M+ users","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2009","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Gosuslugi","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gosuslugi.ru","status":"Not started","summary":"Gosuslugi is Russia's national digital government portal, operated by the Ministry of Digital Development, Communications and Mass Media. It provides Russian citizens with access to a comprehensive range of government services online, including identity verification, tax filings, and social benefits. With over 100 million registered users, it is one of the largest government digital service platforms globally. Due to sanctions imposed by the European Union, the United States, and other jurisdictions in response to the conflict in Ukraine, technical and commercial engagement with this platform is not currently permissible for entities operating under those jurisdictions.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Russia"},{"code":"SA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"28.5M+ (virtually all Saudi citizens)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Nationality","Gender"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"NAFATH","officialDocUrl":"https://www.iam.gov.sa","status":"Not started","summary":"NAFATH is Saudi Arabia's national digital identity platform, operated by the National Information Center (NIC) under the Ministry of Interior. It forms a core component of the Kingdom's Vision 2030 digital transformation agenda. As of early 2025, over 28.5 million individuals are enrolled — encompassing virtually all Saudi citizens. Authentication is supported via facial recognition and fingerprint biometrics through the NAFATH application. The platform is mandatory for government services and is increasingly required for private sector KYC processes. Third-party integration requires approval from the NIC.","useCases":["IDV","AML","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Saudi Arabia"},{"code":"SE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"15% (1,5M out of 9,4M >16)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Other","launchDate":"2017","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Freja eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.frejaeid.com","status":"Pending on Integration","summary":"Freja eID is a Swedish digital identity service provided by Verisec, available primarily in Sweden and also in Denmark. Unlike bank-backed identity solutions, Freja eID does not require a bank account; identity verification is instead performed in person at designated pickup points such as tobacco retailers or post offices. The service is available at two primary assurance levels: Freja eID at a basic level and Freja eID+ at a substantial level, the latter requiring completed in-person identity verification.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected Q4)","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Sweden EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digg.se/","status":"Not started","summary":"Sweden's national EUDI Wallet is under development by the Agency for Digital Government (Digg), coordinating implementation across government stakeholders. The wallet is expected to be available by December 2026, with Sverige-ID — the newly legislated state eID credential passed by the Riksdag in June 2026 — serving as the foundational credential on which the wallet will be built. A publicly available sandbox has not yet been announced. Digg is leading the technical and regulatory groundwork required for full eIDAS 2.0 compliance.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing"]},{"countryStatus":"Announced","estimatedCoverage":"TBD","fieldsReturned":["TBD"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Country","launchDate":"2026-12-01","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS High","name":"Sverige-ID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.digg.se/5.7bd759d319d889532e751b.html","status":"Not started","summary":"Sverige-ID is Sweden's national government-issued digital identity credential, developed by the Swedish Police Authority in collaboration with the Agency for Digital Government (Digg) under the Ministry of Finance. The Act on Government Electronic Identification was passed by the Riksdag in June 2026 and takes effect on December 1, 2026, when applications will open to all citizens and residents aged nine and above. The credential is linked to the national ID card for Swedish citizens and to a special ID card for registered residents; national ID cards issued before December 1, 2026 are not eligible for integration. Sverige-ID is designed as a government alternative to BankID, addressing accessibility gaps for groups who cannot currently obtain BankID, including new arrivals, people with intellectual disabilities, and those without a Swedish bank account. The system meets eIDAS High level of assurance and underpins Sweden's EUDI Wallet implementation, serving as the foundational government credential on which the wallet will be built.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Digital Signing","Age Assurance"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~95% of Swedish adults with bank account","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","ID Number"],"idType":"Bank-backed eID","issuingAuthority":"Private – Bank","launchDate":"2003","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Swedish BankID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.bankid.com","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"Open Beta","summary":"Swedish BankID is Sweden's de facto digital identity standard, operated by a consortium of Swedish banks and used by virtually all Swedish internet users. Authentication is performed via QR code scan on desktop or directly through the BankID mobile application. Availability is tied to bank account ownership, which limits access for non-Swedish residents. Date of birth is not returned as a separate claim; it is encoded within the personnummer but is not extracted as a discrete field.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Sweden"},{"code":"SG","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"82% of population, 97% of Singaporeans and PRs","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","ID Number","Date of Birth","Age","Sex","Email Address","Nationality","Gender","Birth Place","Address","Phone","License Class"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2003 2017 to Private Sector","levelOfAssurance":"Singpass Auth LoA 1-3","name":"Singpass","officialDocUrl":"https://docs.developer.singpass.gov.sg/","varianceCoverage":"Beta","status":"GA","summary":"Singpass is Singapore's national digital identity platform, operated by the Government Technology Agency (GovTech) under the Smart Nation initiative. The MyInfo API functions as a \"Tell Us Once\" data-sharing layer, allowing users to pre-fill forms and share government-held personal data, including NRIC details, address, employment, and tax records with consenting private-sector services, without needing to re-submit documentation each time. Explicit user consent is required per transaction; the verifying party receives the data directly and does not store it independently. The platform currently serves over five million users and facilitates more than 41 million transactions monthly, with integration across more than 2,700 government and private-sector services. Access for businesses is managed through the Singpass Developer and Partner Portal, with a sandbox environment available for testing prior to production. The platform also offers complementary services including Identiface (facial biometric verification) and Verify (in-person QR-based identity confirmation).","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Singapore"},{"code":"SI","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","name":"Slovenia EUDI Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.si","status":"Not started","summary":"Slovenia's national digital identity wallet is under development as part of the EU Digital Identity (EUDI) Wallet mandate. No consumer-facing application is currently available for third-party integration. Slovenia has demonstrated stronger-than-expected progress as of early 2026. Upon launch, the wallet is expected to target eIDAS High level of assurance, in line with EUDI Wallet specifications.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Slovenia"},{"code":"SK","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID + EUDI Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2020","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"eDOKLADY","officialDocUrl":"https://www.slovensko.sk","status":"Not started","summary":"eDOKLADY is Slovakia's government electronic documents application, enabling Slovak citizens to store and present digital versions of their national ID card, driving licence, and other official documents. Digitally presented documents carry full legal equivalence to their physical counterparts. An upgrade to eIDAS 2.0 and EUDI Wallet compliance has been officially confirmed, with eDOKLADY designated as Slovakia's EUDI Wallet implementation. Offline verification functionality is planned for Q2 2026, with full eIDAS 2.0 alignment targeted for December 2026.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Slovakia"},{"code":"SM","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"Announced","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"San Marino eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gov.sm","status":"Not started","summary":"San Marino's national identity card serves as the primary identification document for citizens of the republic, issued by the Civil Status Office. The card is accepted as a travel document within the European Union, reflecting San Marino's close institutional ties with Italy and its participation in the EU customs union. San Marino is a republic with a population of approximately 34,000. Digital identity services are currently accessible through government-operated channels; broader online integration infrastructure is very limited.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"San Marino"},{"code":"TH","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"43% (Covers banked adult Thai citizens)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Identity Infrastructure","issuingAuthority":"National – Bank","launchDate":"2019 Live transactions started w commercial banks","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"NDID","officialDocUrl":"https://ndid.co.th/en","status":"Researching","summary":"NDID (National Digital ID Co., Ltd.) is a blockchain-based identity infrastructure backed by the Bank of Thailand and majority-owned by financial sector shareholders. It functions as a trust relay between identity providers, typically commercial banks where a user has already completed KYC service relying parties rather than as a consumer-facing identity credential in its own right. ThaID has been integrated into the NDID platform in a SaaS model, with transaction logs recorded on-chain, allowing relying parties to access government-issued identity verification alongside bank-held KYC data through a single connection. Both systems are currently restricted to Thai citizens, with the Phase 2 Digital ID Framework targeting extension to foreign residents and migrant workers through 2027.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"26%","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","Portrait"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"ThaID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.bora.dopa.go.th/app-thaid/","status":"Researching","summary":"ThaID is a mobile application developed by the Department of Provincial Administration (DOPA) under Thailand's Ministry of Interior, providing Thai citizens with a digital form of their national identity card. The system includes a facial biometric verification service that submits a citizen's ID number and facial image for comparison against DOPA's civil registration biometric database, returning a percentage match score rather than a binary result. ThaID is currently restricted to Thai citizens; Phase 2 of the national Digital ID Framework (2025–2027) aims to extend coverage to foreign residents and migrant workers, though implementation details remain in development. Relying parties wishing to access ThaID must be separately authorised as ThaID service providers by DOPA.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Thailand"},{"code":"TR","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~65M+ registered users (~75% of Turkish adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Government Portal","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2008","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"e-Devlet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.turkiye.gov.tr","status":"Not started","summary":"e-Devlet (e-Government Gateway) is Turkey's national digital government platform, operated by the Ministry of Interior, providing citizens with access to a comprehensive range of government services online using their national identity card. As of April 2026, Turkey is finalising legislation requiring social media platforms to implement identity verification via e-Devlet, reflecting the platform's expanding role in digital regulation. Biometric national identity cards are widely issued across the population. The platform operates under Turkish national standards and is not subject to the eIDAS regulatory framework.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Turkey"},{"code":"UA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"21M+ users (~50% of Ukrainian adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number","Tax ID"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2020","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Diia","officialDocUrl":"https://www.diia.gov.ua","status":"Not started","summary":"Diia is Ukraine's national digital identity wallet, operated by the Ministry of Digital Transformation. With over 21 million registered users, it is among the most advanced digital identity systems in the world. The wallet provides digital representations of the national passport, identity card, driving licence, vehicle registration, and additional official documents, all of which carry full legal equivalence to their physical counterparts. As an EU candidate country since 2022, Ukraine is exploring alignment of Diia with the EUDI Wallet framework.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","Age Assurance"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Ukraine"},{"code":"US","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (varies by state)","estimatedCoverage":"77% of US as of mid 2025","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","License Number"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"Varies by state","levelOfAssurance":"US NIST IAL2","name":"DMV via Database Verification","officialDocUrl":"https://variance.co","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"DMV Database Verification is a United States identity verification service that validates driver's licence data against state Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) records, without requiring the user to physically present a document. Coverage varies by state, as participation in the programme is determined at the state level rather than federally. The service is designed to support identity verification workflows as a standalone check or in combination with document and biometric verification methods.","useCases":["IDV","AML"]},{"countryStatus":"GA (13+ states)","estimatedCoverage":"~2M+ users across 13+ active states (~2% of eligible US adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","License Number","Portrait","Age Verification"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021","levelOfAssurance":"US NIST IAL2","name":"mDL via Apple Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.apple.com/wallet","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"Mobile driver's licences (mDLs) stored in Apple Wallet are US state-issued digital credentials presented via NFC. The solution is compliant with ISO 18013-5, with data that is end-to-end encrypted and tamper-proof. Users authenticate via Face ID or Touch ID prior to presentation. As of mid-2025, 13–14 US states and Puerto Rico have active mDL programmes. Adoption remains limited by state-level availability, OEM platform support, and a currently narrow set of accepted use cases.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]},{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"~600k users in California (~2% of CA adults)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Address","License Number","Portrait"],"idType":"Document Verification","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2022","levelOfAssurance":"US NIST IAL2","name":"mDL via CA DMV Wallet","officialDocUrl":"https://www.dmv.ca.gov","status":"Closed Beta","summary":"The California DMV Wallet is a state-issued digital driver's licence application operated directly by the California Department of Motor Vehicles (CA DMV). Unlike OEM wallet solutions, the CA DMV Wallet enables tamper-proof verification of official DMV credentials without reliance on third-party platform providers, offering broader mDL coverage within California. The model is expected to inform similar state-operated wallet initiatives in other large US states.","useCases":["IDV","Age Verification"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"United States"},{"code":"UY","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2023","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula de Identidad Digital","officialDocUrl":"https://www.gub.uy","status":"Not started","summary":"Uruguay's national identity card (Cédula de Identidad) is issued by the National Civil Identification Directorate (DNIC) under the Ministry of the Interior. A digital version has been available since 2023 via the Gub.uy government portal and the MiDNI application, enabling citizens to present their identity credentials digitally. Uruguay has one of the highest rates of internet penetration and digital government service adoption in Latin America, with the Agencia de Gobierno Electrónico y Sociedad de la Información y del Conocimiento (AGESIC) coordinating the national digital identity strategy. The system provides access to over 500 government services online.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Uruguay"},{"code":"VE","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"Cédula de Identidad","officialDocUrl":"https://www.saime.gob.ve","status":"Not started","summary":"Venezuela's national identity card (Cédula de Identidad) is issued by the National Electoral Council (CNE) and the Office of Identification and Migration (SAIME). A digital verification service exists via the SAIME portal. Due to the political situation in Venezuela and the sanctions imposed by the European Union, the United States, and other jurisdictions, technical and commercial engagement with Venezuelan government digital systems presents significant compliance and operational risks for international organisations.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Venezuela"},{"code":"VN","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA","estimatedCoverage":"68% of population","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","Portrait","Birth Place","Address"],"idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2021 Level 2 accounts / Private sector banking integration -- Jan 2025","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"VNeID","officialDocUrl":"https://vneid.gov.vn","status":"Researching","summary":"VNeID (Vietnam Electronic Identification) is Vietnam's national digital identity platform, developed and operated by the Ministry of Public Security's National Population Data Center. It is anchored to Vietnam's chip-based Citizen Identification Card and assigns a unique identifier tied to a national population database of 107 million records. The platform supports two verification levels: Level 1 (basic identity confirmation) and Level 2 (full biometric verification), with Level 2 required for regulated financial services. From January 2025, biometric authentication via VNeID became mandatory for online banking transactions; from January 2026, the requirement extended to opening bank accounts and issuing payment cards. The platform was extended to foreign nationals from July 2025. As of late 2025, VNeID had approximately 67 million verified digital accounts and was integrated with 12 major banks and 15 government ministries. The government has set a target of full national digital identity coverage by 2026, with VNeID positioned as the central gateway for citizen-state interactions.","useCases":["IDV","KYC","Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Vietnam"},{"code":"XK","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"GA (early adoption)","fieldsReturned":["First Name","Last Name","Date of Birth","ID Number"],"idType":"Government Wallet","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2024","levelOfAssurance":"eIDAS Substantial","name":"Kosovo eID","officialDocUrl":"https://www.rks-gov.net","status":"Not started","summary":"Kosovo's national eID platform (eID Kosova) was developed under the EU4Innovation project and handed over to the Ministry of Economy for public launch in mid-2024. The platform includes an electronic signature function and an identity wallet. It is explicitly designed to comply with eIDAS 2.0 and GDPR standards, despite Kosovo not being an EU member state. The platform supports authentication for a broad range of digital services including e-commerce, e-banking, e-health, and e-government. As an EU candidate country, Kosovo is targeting EUDI Wallet alignment by the extended 2027 deadline.","useCases":["Government Services"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"Kosovo"},{"code":"ZA","digitalIds":[{"countryStatus":"In Development","idType":"National eID","issuingAuthority":"Government","launchDate":"2026 (expected)","levelOfAssurance":"National Standard","name":"SmartID / MyMzansi","officialDocUrl":"https://www.dha.gov.za","status":"Not started","summary":"South Africa's digital identity programme is anchored to the SmartID card, issued by the Department of Home Affairs (DHA), and is undergoing a significant expansion as part of the MyMzansi Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI) roadmap announced in 2025. President Cyril Ramaphosa committed to launching a functional national digital ID system before the end of 2026. The programme comprises a PKI-based identity platform, a certificate authority, digital verifiable credentials, and a digital wallet secured by biometric authentication. Nine major South African banks are already participating in the digitised SmartID issuance process. Draft regulations for a new five-year validity digital ID were gazetted in May 2026. The National Identification and Registration Bill is being prepared to provide the legislative foundation for the new system.","useCases":["IDV","Government Services","KYC"]}],"lastUpdated":"2026-06","name":"South Africa"}]}